{
  "doc_id": "40495",
  "text": "Similar auto-regulatory genetic networks were also described for other organisms, including Drosophila [CITATION_1] , zebrafish [CITATION_2] and cyanobacteria [CITATION_3] , although most likely from diverse evolutionary origins [CITATION_4] . The intricacy of the different clock networks is variable in its complexity, ranging from a three elements network in cyanobacteria to the above described 14 genes network for mammals. It is worth noticing that non-transcriptional clocks were described in red blood cells which may generate oscillations in the absence of transcription [CITATION_5] , but these are beyond the scope of this review.",
